Name: Ehlers-Danlos syndrome progeroid type
Definition: An Ehlers-Danlos syndrome that is characterized by aged appearance

Name: type I Ehlers-Danlos syndrome
Definition: A myopathy characterized by abnormally located  nuclei in skeletal muscle cells. The nuclei are located in the center of the cell

Name: autosomal dominant type IV Ehlers-Danlos syndrome
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves the accumulation of argininosuccinic acid (ASA) in the blood and urine.

Name: type III Ehlers-Danlos syndrome
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves the accumulation of argininosuccinic acid (ASA) in the blood and urine.

Name: autosomal recessive type IV Ehlers-Danlos syndrome
Definition: An amino acid metabolic disorder that involves the accumulation of argininosuccinic acid (ASA) in the blood and urine.

Name: brittle cornea syndrome
Definition: An acrocephalosyndactylia that has_material_basis_in a genetic mutation in the TWIST1 gene which results_in premature fusion located_in skull.
